Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on automatic speech recognition (ASR) using self-attention networks, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as ASR involves processing audio signals. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a RNN-free end-to-end model using self-attention networks, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as ASR is a subfield of AI and the paper proposes a novel model for this task. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing) is another possible category as ASR involves processing audio signals, but it is less likely than cs.CL and cs.SD.
